OL,3,CHealth visitors left with 'no choice'
OL,4,Cbut strike action amid pay banding row
OL,6,FUnite says health visitors, who do
OL,7,Fvital community outreach work for new
OL,8,Fmothers and families, are furious that
OL,9,Fthey are only being paid as band six
OL,10,Fworkers. This is despite internal job
OL,11,Fgrading now matching them as a band
OL,12,Fseven acknowledging a masters
OL,13,Fqualification, the union added.
OL,15,FAs a result, health visitors are
OL,16,Ftaking strike action from 23 February
OL,17,Fto 20 March.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1771879288
OL,3,CHealth visitors left with 'no choice'
OL,4,Cbut strike action amid pay banding row
OL,6,FUnite general secretary Sharon Graham
OL,7,Fsaid: "This is an outrageous ploy from
OL,8,Fa health board to try and avoid paying
OL,9,Fits essential staff the money they are
OL,10,Fworth.
OL,12,F"This is a significant pay difference
OL,13,Fthat has left our members undervalued
OL,14,Fand underpaid. They have been left
OL,15,Fwith little choice but to take strike
OL,16,Faction and will have the full support
OL,17,Fof Unite in this dispute."
OL,26,@tD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/12
